Comment:
The last time I traveled, I was did not take my dog out as I should because of a fear of missing my connecting flight.  {I was told I would need to go outside the terminal  (due to the time and distance involved in geting to a relief area that was located outside the sterile area of the terminal)  and needing to have gone back through a screening at the TSA security checkpoint before I would have been allowed to return to the gate area with my service dog.}  

        Please make the service animal relief area inside the sterile area to ensure time and distance are not an issue.

In the past, I have seen dogs have a bathroom accident due to their not being able to use the bathroom when need.  Some dogs are like the humans who become upset and need to use the bathroom more because of traveling.
